Key Match Events: Miller and Stubbs added 65 for the fifth wicket to lift South Africa from 12 for 4
Miller stayed the course and remained unbeaten on 59, flicking on his best six-hitting self in the penultimate over
Stubbs finally shrug off the pressure with a hoick for six off Vikramjit Singh, and then launched van Beek down the ground three balls later
Miller finished the game with a sequence of 2, 0, 4 and 6 in the penultimate over
Post-Match Reflections: Miller had tamed the demons of Adelaide 2022
Engelbrecht's patient knock and his 54-run association with van Beek helped Netherlands make a match out of it
Miscellaneous Highlights: Quinton de Kock was run out without facing a ball
Reeza Hendricks got a peach from Logan van Beek that angled in and straightened to hit the top of off
Vivian Kingma had the first of a double when he strangled Aiden Markram down leg to leave South Africa 3 for 3
Heinrich Klaasen's rush of blood had him picking out Tim Pringle attempting a pull off Kingma
Bas de Leede came on in the 11th, Stubbs gave him the charge and enjoyed a massive slice of luck as a thick inside edge flew wide of the midwicket fielder
A big hit down the ground off left-arm spinner Pringle only just eluded the long-on fielder in the 12th over with South Africa still needing 57 off 50
Paul van Meekeren delivered a maiden over to Miller, and the pressure showed when Stubbs holed out to deep midwicket in the next, off Bas de Leede
van Beek came back after being walloped for six by Miller to dismiss Marco Jansen
Others: South Africa made heavy weather of a modest chase in New York
The game came down to 16 off 12 in the penultimate over
Netherlands were put in to bat seemingly because South Africa wanted to exploit the morning conditions
Engelbrecht top-scored with a 45-ball 40 on surface where the next best among the top seven was 12
